1. Definition and Examples of Predatory Stalking Behavior

Predatory stalking involves persistent online behavior that is designed to intimidate, harass, or cause distress to a targeted individual. It can include activities like following someone on social media platforms, sending unwanted messages or images, sharing private information, or creating false accounts to imitate the targeted person. The perpetrator may gain this information by exploiting social media platform vulnerabilities, or by exploiting information that the target willingly shares on their own social media accounts."
