2. If the kettle has a removable filter, remove it and soak it in the mixture. This will help to dissolve the deposits inside the filter.

3. If the kettle has a built-in filter, pour the mixture into the kettle and turn it on to heat it up. This will help to dissolve the deposits.

4. After the mixture has boiled, let it sit in the kettle for 1-2 hours. This will give the mixture time to work on dissolving any remaining deposits.

5. After the waiting period, turn off the kettle and let it cool down. Then, discard the vinegar and water mixture.

6. Fill the kettle with fresh water and boil it. This will help to rinse out any remaining vinegar and deposits.

7. You can now use the kettle as usual.

Remember, white vinegar is a natural and safe solution for dissolving hard water deposits. However, if you prefer to use a different method, there are other options available, such as lemon juice and baking soda, or citric acid."
